('urn:li:lyndaVideo:(urn:li:lyndaCourse:786354,5037716)', '2020-07-18T16:21:29.000Z', '{"urn":"urn:li:lyndaVideo:(urn:li:lyndaCourse:786354,5037716)","title":{"value":"Gap analysis and scope"},"details":{"urls":{"webLaunch":"https://www.linkedin.com/learning/business-process-improvement/gap-analysis-and-scope"},"images":{},"timeToComplete":{"duration":146},"descriptionIncludingHtml":{"value":"Learn to illustrate the difference between your present and desired states so you can accurately identify the scope of your improvement project."}}}'),
('urn:li:lyndaVideo:(urn:li:lyndaCourse:373782,459931)', '2020-07-18T16:21:30.000Z', '{"urn":"urn:li:lyndaVideo:(urn:li:lyndaCourse:373782,459931)","title":{"value":"Developing a project plan"},"details":{"urls":{"webLaunch":"https://www.linkedin.com/learning/note-taking-for-business-professionals/developing-a-project-plan"},"images":{},"timeToComplete":{"duration":108}}}'),
('urn:li:lyndaVideo:(urn:li:lyndaCourse:456826,505802)', '2020-07-18T16:21:31.000Z', '{"urn":"urn:li:lyndaVideo:(urn:li:lyndaCourse:456826,505802)","title":{"value":"Evaluate the change"},"details":{"urls":{"webLaunch":"https://www.linkedin.com/learning/change-management-foundations/evaluate-the-change"},"images":{},"timeToComplete":{"duration":215},"descriptionIncludingHtml":{"value":"Where you measure, you also reveal. The changes you put in place can create visible improvement in your business and reveal opportunities for new changes. In this video, Bob McGannon explores items that an evaluation of your changes can reveal including; bottleneck shifts, revealed weaknesses and new found energy for further changes. "}}}'),
('urn:li:lyndaVideo:(urn:li:lyndaCourse:784282,5038750)', '2020-07-18T16:21:32.000Z', '{"urn":"urn:li:lyndaVideo:(urn:li:lyndaCourse:784282,5038750)","title":{"value":"Evaluating new opportunities"},"details":{"urls":{"webLaunch":"https://www.linkedin.com/learning/strategic-focus-for-managers/evaluating-new-opportunities"},"images":{},"timeToComplete":{"duration":119},"descriptionIncludingHtml":{"value":"New opportunities come along all the time. Resist the urge to jump on the next new thing, and rely on your prioritization processes to assess new ideas. Remember: if you add something new to your list, you either need to add resources to work on it or you should stop working on something else or finish another task before starting a new one. Failure to do so leads to the inevitable burnout of your team."}}}'),
('urn:li:lyndaVideo:(urn:li:lyndaCourse:450184,508590)', '2020-07-18T16:21:33.000Z', '{"urn":"urn:li:lyndaVideo:(urn:li:lyndaCourse:450184,508590)","title":{"value":"Organizational change"},"details":{"urls":{"webLaunch":"https://www.linkedin.com/learning/project-management-technical-projects/organizational-change"},"images":{},"timeToComplete":{"duration":244},"descriptionIncludingHtml":{"value":"Significant organizational change can be brought about by your technology projects, and if you are not careful, chaos can be created. In this video, Bob McGannon takes you through the steps to imbed organizational change including having a plan, communication, evaluation of roles, training and measuring the effectiveness of your solution. In addition, he will explore obstacles to progress including potential power shifts, current experts preserving their roles, and other resistant stakeholders."}}}'),
('urn:li:lyndaVideo:(urn:li:lyndaCourse:456826,505778)', '2020-07-18T16:21:33.000Z', '{"urn":"urn:li:lyndaVideo:(urn:li:lyndaCourse:456826,505778)","title":{"value":"Change management in projects"},"details":{"urls":{"webLaunch":"https://www.linkedin.com/learning/change-management-foundations/change-management-in-projects"},"images":{},"timeToComplete":{"duration":269},"descriptionIncludingHtml":{"value":"Change management is full of activities you cannot measure objectively, and even if you could, the effectiveness of change activities varies from person to person. In this video, Bob McGannon shares the steps he uses when creating a change management plan for his projects, including how to formulate and plan the change, communicate the change, provide education, and assessing new or differing roles. In addition, the measurements that can be put in place for staff to assess the effectiveness of the changed processes are reviewed."}}}'),
('urn:li:lyndaVideo:(urn:li:lyndaCourse:765311,2228235)', '2020-07-18T16:21:34.000Z', '{"urn":"urn:li:lyndaVideo:(urn:li:lyndaCourse:765311,2228235)","title":{"value":"How to manage project change"},"details":{"urls":{"webLaunch":"https://www.linkedin.com/learning/project-management-foundations-4/how-to-manage-project-change-3"},"images":{},"timeToComplete":{"duration":147},"descriptionIncludingHtml":{"value":"When the project is underway, changes are bound to arise. Project management trainer and consultant Bonnie Biafore describes the process for managing change requests including receiving requests, evaluating and estimating them, getting approval, and tracking their progress. Bonnie explains what to do in special cases like emergencies or change requests with really big impact."}}}'),
('urn:li:lyndaVideo:(urn:li:lyndaCourse:515156,594900)', '2020-07-18T16:21:34.000Z', '{"urn":"urn:li:lyndaVideo:(urn:li:lyndaCourse:515156,594900)","title":{"value":"How to plan for change"},"details":{"urls":{"webLaunch":"https://www.linkedin.com/learning/handling-workplace-change-as-an-employee/how-to-plan-for-change"},"images":{},"timeToComplete":{"duration":193},"descriptionIncludingHtml":{"value":"Learn how the best cure for worry is planning. Work with others to make a plan. Get as much information as you can. Consider options and make sure you include positive outcomes of the change. Have a clear objective and consider staying, leaving, or retiring."}}}'),
('urn:li:lyndaVideo:(urn:li:lyndaCourse:456826,505783)', '2020-07-18T16:21:35.000Z', '{"urn":"urn:li:lyndaVideo:(urn:li:lyndaCourse:456826,505783)","title":{"value":"Create a change plan"},"details":{"urls":{"webLaunch":"https://www.linkedin.com/learning/change-management-foundations/create-a-change-plan"},"images":{},"timeToComplete":{"duration":239},"descriptionIncludingHtml":{"value":"Once you have performed change formulation and refinement, your real work begins – you need to plan carefully and start the process of making your change vision a reality. In this video, change manager Bob McGannon gives you tips for creating a change plan. Tips include treating the change plan as a project; and focusing on developing, maintaining and monitoring change support systems. In addition, the concept of creating a resistance plan is presented."}}}'),
('urn:li:lyndaVideo:(urn:li:lyndaCourse:802843,3502086)', '2020-07-18T16:21:35.000Z', '{"urn":"urn:li:lyndaVideo:(urn:li:lyndaCourse:802843,3502086)","title":{"value":"Planning change communications"},"details":{"urls":{"webLaunch":"https://www.linkedin.com/learning/change-management-for-projects/planning-change-communications"},"images":{},"timeToComplete":{"duration":184},"descriptionIncludingHtml":{"value":"In this video,Claudine Peet shows you how to plan your communications so that every stakeholder is communicated with at the right time in the right way. Create a communication plan to communicate the change to all affected stakeholders using the stakeholder analysis."}}}'),
